      "number": 991,
      "title": "[FIX] Improve safety in CartActionBean: null workingItemId check + narrow exception handling",
      "url": "https://github.com/mybatis/jpetstore-6/issues/991",
      "description_message": "@hazendaz \nIn CartActionBean:\nValidate workingItemId before use\nMethods like addItemToCart() and removeItemFromCart() assume workingItemId is always set.\nIf it is null or blank (e.g., due to a malformed request), these methods may throw an NPE or return confusing results.\nMy fix will be add a null/blank check early and return an error resolution with a clear message when workingItemId is invalid.\n\n\nNarrow exception handling in updateCartQuantities()\nThe code currently does catch (Exception e) and ignores it.\nThis can swallow unexpected errors.\nProposal: catch only NumberFormatException (the intended case of bad user input) and optionally add guardrails for extreme values\n\nLet me know if I can create a PR and do a quick fix",
      "created_at": "2025-09-23T05:53:46Z",
      "closed_at": "2026-01-25T17:31:47Z",
